          "name": "Indian River Lagoon Seagrass Recovery",
          "location": "Indian River Lagoon, Florida (2020-present)",
          "description": "156-mile estuary system, lost 58% of seagrass (47,000 acres) between 2011-2019. Economic impact: Seagrass loss cost $2.1 billion in economic damage, property values declined 15-25%. Recovery efforts: $480 million restoration initiative funded by state and federal sources. Deployed 15 wave break installations reducing turbidity by 65%, installed 127 oyster reefs for nutrient filtration, planted 5,000 acres using innovative 'seed pod' technology. Results: 30% seagrass recovery in treatment areas, manatee populations stabilizing after 1,101 deaths in 2021, property values recovering 8% annually in restoration zones, water clarity improved 40% in managed areas. Financial returns: Tourism recovery $300M annual increase, property tax base $1.2B recovered value, carbon credits $4.5M annually from verified sequestration.",
