          "location": "Louisiana (Ongoing)",
          "description": "Uses Construction Management At-Risk (CMAR) contracting for massive projects (e.g., Chandeleur Islands) to integrate the construction contractor into the early design phase. Mobile needs this model to expedite the $60M Dauphin Island West End Nourishment and complex MsCIP projects, reducing financial risk and ensuring constructability. The CMAR model allows for more efficient completion of large restoration projects and leverages private expertise to manage project costs.",
          "reference": "https://coastal.la.gov/news/cmar-contractor-selected-for-chandeleur-island-restoration-project/"
